Explanation:
We use a two-dimensional array (dp) to store the number of palindromic substrings ending at each index. We iterate through the string once to populate the dp array. Then, we return the value at the bottom-right corner (dp[0][n-1]) which represents the total number of palindromic substrings in the string.

